<title>CANADA: Ballard shares jump on alliances.</title>
<headline>Ballard shares jump on alliances.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Ballard Power Systems Inc jumped in early trade on Monday, extending a climb that has seen the fuel cell development firm gain more than 25 percent in two weeks.</p>
<p>Analysts said Ballard's recent success in attracting partners, including an alliance approved last week with Daimler-Benz AG under which Ballard sold a 25 percent stake to Daimler, caught the market's attention. &quot;Over the past couple of weeks (Ballard) has really settled into the market...it's not just a concept stock anymore...but a money-generating proposition,&quot; one analyst said.</p>
</text>
